  "text": "Proof. We assume C is given a factorization instance N for a product of unknown p and q, and obtain the result of p or q with a non-negligible probability. C plays with A as follows. Firstly, C selects a ∈ Z * N , such as a non-cubic residue and a secure parameter 160 (the length of has been discussed and suggested in [CITATION_1] ), and sends (N, a, ) to A as mpk. C manages several lists: one signature list and three hash lists.",
